Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no
need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{},
then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway
through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Heat the @butter{20%g} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once melted, add the onion, season with salt and pepper and fry, stirring occasionally,
until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}. Add the @sugar{1%tsp} and cook until caramelised,
~{1-2%minutes} more.

While the onion fries, trim the @Brussels sprouts{200%g} and halve through the root.
Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the Brussels sprouts onto a baking tray. Drizzle over some oil and season with salt
and pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the chips have 20 mins remaining, add the sprouts the oven and roast on the middle
shelf until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Turn the sprouts halfway through and toss in the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}, then return
to the oven for the remaining roasting time.

When the onion has caramelised, add the @sliced mushrooms{180%g} to the pan. Fry,
stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Grate the @mature cheddar
cheese{80%g}. Halve the @ciabatta{2}.

Add the garlic to the mushrooms for the last min of cooking time and fry, ~{1%minute}.

Spoon the mushrooms onto the base of each ciabatta. Top with the cheese, then sandwich
shut with the ciabatta lids and firmly press all the ingredients inside.

Give the frying pan a quick wipe, then add a drizzle of oil and return to a medium-high
heat.

Once hot, add the sandwiches, pressing down with a #spatula{} or #heavy-bottomed pan{}.
Cook, pressing occasionally, until the bread is golden and toasted and the cheese has
melted, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

Once the sprouts are roasted, drizzle over the @honey{1%tbsp} and toss until coated.

Once the chips are ready, sprinkle over the @truffle zest{1%sachet} and toss together.

When everything's ready, share the mushroom grilled cheese sandwiches between your
plates.

Serve the honey-balsamic Brussels sprouts and truffle chips alongside with @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}
for dipping.

Enjoy!